</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD LAPPER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The International Finance Corporation yesterday approved a guarantee of up
to Dollars 10m for the Russian Trade Enhancement Facility, a new facility
that will partially guarantee the credit risk of Russian banks engaged in
trade finance.
The facility, the first of its type to be supported by the International
Finance Corporation is expected to guarantee up to Dollars 2.4bn of Russian
trade.
ABN AMRO, the Dutch bank, is co-guaranteeing the facility and will match,
dollar for dollar, the corporation's exposure on each transaction.
