<HEADLINE>
FT  11 NOV 94 / International Company News: Heinz examining ways to invest
in S Africa
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   JOHANNESBURG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
US food group HJ Heinz is looking into ways to invest in South Africa,
chairman Mr Tony O'Reilly said, Reuter reports from Johannesburg. He said
Heinz's chief financial officer Mr David Williams was heading a team
reviewing options.
'We are reviewing various ways in which obviously we can invest in what we
consider. . . an economy that will be expanding over the next few years,' Mr
O'Reilly said.
Mr O'Reilly's Irish-based Independent Newspapers group holds 39.9 per cent
of South Africa's Argus Newspapers.
