FT  11 NOV 94 / International Company News: Highlands Gold shares worth
ADollars 38m sold
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Stockbroker County NatWest said it had completed transactions totalling 28m
shares, or 5 per cent, in Papua New Guinea gold miner Highlands Gold at
ADollars 1.38 a share, Reuter reports from Sydney. The broker would not,
however, disclose the buyer or the seller of the Highlands shares, which
were worth ADollars 38.64m (USDollars 29.2m).
MIM Holdings, the Queensland-based metals group which owns 65 per cent of
Highlands, said it was not behind the transaction. MIM has sold most of its
equity investments over the past 12 months as part of a strategy of putting
all assets under review.
Highlands shares closed 3 cents lower at ADollars 1.45, on a turnover of
29.03m, on the Australian Stock Exchange.
