<HEADLINE>
FT  11 NOV 94 / UK Company News: Difficult second quarter at Parkland
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Parkland Group, the woollen yarn and worsted cloth maker, saw pre-tax
profits fall from Pounds 970,000 to Pounds 950,000 in the six months to
September 2, after a difficult second quarter.
However, profits on continuing operations, after taking account of the sale
of its interest in Company Image, improved by 7 per cent to Pounds 1.02m.
Mr Denis Greenwood, chairman, said the second quarter was characterised by
late contracting from many large customers and longer term concerns about
raw material price pressures.
'Although this very demanding trading environment still prevails in many of
our markets, order levels and production have improved substantially in
recent weeks,' he added.
Parkland also announced that it was paying Pounds 110,000 in shares to
acquire Firthmill, a textile importer. In addition, Pounds 40,000 loans to
the vendors will be repaid on completion.
Turnover fell from Pounds 29.3m to Pounds 25.8m, including Pounds 1.35m
(Pounds 3.8m) from discontinued operations. Earnings per share were 10.2p
(10.3p) and the interim dividend is held at 2p.
