FT  11 NOV 94 / Observer: Art for eats' sake
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Marcel Duchamp would turn in his grave; he once sent shivers down the spine
of the art world by putting on an exhibition which included a lavatory. Tame
stuff by comparison with the latest offering from Chinese artist Huang Yon
Ping at Paris's Georges Pompidou centre.
On Tuesday he assembled a group of spiders, scorpions, snakes and toads in
an exhibition wittily entitled Hors Limites, l'art et la vie, 1952-1994 -
Beyond Limits, art and life. They were to eat one another, making a
statement on humankind's dog-eat-dog world. Unfortunately, police closed the
exhibition yesterday using laws forbidding cruelty to animals.
