<HEADLINE>
FT  11 NOV 94 / Static water demand forecast
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Water companies expect virtually no overall growth in water demand over the
next 20 years, a summary of forecasts prepared by Ofwat, the industry
regulator, shows.
The forecasts suggest that a strong increase in demand by households will be
offset by several factors. These include a 21 per cent fall in leakage, a 5
per cent fall in demand from industry and a 33 per cent rise in metered
households.
