<HEADLINE>
FT  10 NOV 94 / International Company News: Moody's downgrades Eli Lilly to
Aa3
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP-DJ
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Moody's, the US credit rating agency, has lowered the long-term debt ratings
of Eli Lilly, the US drugs company, to Aa3 from Aa1, affecting about Dollars
825m of debt securities, AP-DJ reports.
The downgrade concludes a review begun on July 11, after Lilly revealed its
intention to purchase the PCS Health Systems business from McKesson, the US
healthcare group, for Dollars 4bn. Moody's said the downgrade recognised the
heavy debt burden Lilly would undertake to complete the acquisition as well
as the uncertainty whether incremental profits attributable to PCS would
generate attractive investment returns.
