<TEXT>
Brascan, a holding company controlled by Toronto's Bronfman family and their
senior managers, has reported an improved third-quarter performance, due
mainly to stronger commodity markets, writes Bernard Simon in Toronto.
Earnings totalled CDollars 31m (USDollars 23m), or 31 cents a share,
compared with a CDollars 19m loss, or 20 cents, a year earlier. Revenues
climbed to CDollars 1.65bn from CDollars 1.26bn. Brascan forecast a further
improvement for the rest of this year and 1995, based on expectations of
continuing growth in the global economy
