FT  10 NOV 94 / World Stock Markets: Mexico
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The bolsa shed some of its earlier gains after market expectations of an
alliance between AT&amp;T and Telmex were broken when AT&amp;T said it was setting
up a Dollars 1bn telecommunications venture with Grupo Industrial Alfa.
Traders said the market was buying Telmex ahead of AT&amp;T's announcement but
guessed wrong. 'The announcement that the alliance was with Alfa halted the
demand for Telmex and that moderated the market's advance,' one said. But
the news boosted Alfa, which advanced 5 per cent. Telmex 'L' series shares -
those available to foreign investors - were off 1.02 per cent at 9.74 new
pesos.
The IPC index closed only 7.0 points up at 2,618.94 after a high of 2,632.
Volume was 1.12bn new pesos on 80.8m shares traded.
