<HEADLINE>
FT  10 NOV 94 / World Stock Markets: Brazil
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sao Paulo finished 2.1 per cent stronger in moderate trade after equity
prices were led forward by Telebras, the state telecom, which posted
positive results for the first nine months. The Bovespa index rose 1,029 to
48,850, while turnover amounted to RDollars 267.3m.
Telebras preferred put on 5.0 per cent at RDollars 42 after the group posted
a better than expected RDollars 710.8m net profit in the January-September
period.
