<HEADLINE>
FT  10 NOV 94 / UK Company News: Villiers cuts loss to Pounds 1.54m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Villiers Group, the USM-traded specialist engineering company, reported
pre-tax losses reduced from Pounds 2.83m to Pounds 1.54m for the year to
July 31. Turnover was 45 per cent ahead at Pounds 2.72m, compared with a
restated Pounds 1.87m.
Acquisitions contributed Pounds 1.21m to sales. Operating profits totalled
Pounds 11,000 (Pounds 338,000 loss).
The company, which is US-based, said its continuing operations had been
profitable since January. Following the disposal in June of its Starks Field
oil operations for Dollars 2.5m (Pounds 1.52m), its operating accounts
consisted entirely of engineering business. The second half had made a
positive overall contribution, reducing the Pounds 1.86m loss reported at
interim stage.
Losses per share improved from an adjusted 5.48p to 1.49p.
</TEXT>
