<HEADLINE>
FT  10 NOV 94 / UK Company News: Ingham falls to Pounds 853,000 after
provision
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Ingham, the York-based motor parts, worsted spinning and property group,
reported a 42 per cent fall in pre-tax profits, from Pounds 1.47m to Pounds
853,000, for the six months to end September.
Turnover was slightly ahead at Pounds 13.9m (Pounds 13.6m).
The result included the provision for an exceptional administrative expense
of Pounds 210,000. This was in respect of potential compensation payable to
Mr Nicholas McMahon Turner, the former chief executive, for loss of office.
Profits before tax and interest slipped in both the motor group and the
property division, but more than doubled for the group's spinning company,
in spite of a steady rise in wool prices.
Earnings per share were down from 7.1p to 3.2p, with the interim dividend
unchanged at 1.75p.
</TEXT>
