FT  10 NOV 94 / Observer: Gegarbaged
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The French may be building barricades to preserve their language from
Anglo-Saxon barbarisms - but what about the Germans?
The language of Goethe, Schiller and Boris Becker is in danger of being
eroded by influences from beyond Europe's mainland. Gefounded and
gementioned - as in 'our company was gefounded' (founded) or 'will we be
gementioned?' (mentioned) - are two newcomers assaulting sensitive German
ears.
Gemanaged is an old one, as are gehandikapt and gekidnappt. Any suggestions
for others? Gebreakfasted, getroubled and gesacked immediately spring to
mind.
